title: Assault charge at restaurant in Byram
title_page: Assault charge at restaurant in Byram
maintext:
GREENWICH — Police were called to the Greek Kitchen in the Byram section Friday night of town of a report of an assault.
Officers said a Greenwich man had shoved another person and grabbed his shirt around the neck in a way that led to choking.
Seth Bladimirsquy, 51, of Henry Street was charged with assault, strangulation and disorderly conduct. Bail was set at $1,000.
